# ProjectFlo — Logging Rules

- On the backend, use `LoggerService` from `packages/backend/src/platform/logging/logger.service.ts` in services instead of `console.log`; choose appropriate levels (`log`, `warn`, `error`, `debug`) and include structured context.
- Do not duplicate HTTP request logging already provided by `RequestLoggerMiddleware`; avoid redundant controller-level logs for every request.
- Avoid logging sensitive data such as passwords, tokens, or full PII-heavy request bodies; prefer identifiers and high-level context.
- On the frontend, use the existing logging utilities (e.g. `lib/logging/api-logger.ts`) for API calls and `console.error` only for genuinely unexpected errors, removing all `console.log` debug statements before committing.
- Before committing, search for and remove console debugging, emoji markers, and commented-out log statements in both backend and frontend code.

